 :zapped: adj. Spicy. This term is used to distinguish between food that is
hot (in temperature) and food that is spicy-hot. For example, the Chinese
appetizer Bon Bon Chicken is a kind of chicken salad that is cold but zapped;
by contrast, {vanilla} wonton soup is hot but not zapped. see also {oriental
food}, {laser chicken}. see {zap}, senses 1 and 2.